President Biden is set to meet with President Lula of Brazil to announce the U.S.-Brazil Partnership for Workers' Rights. This will be the second time the two presidents have met, and the initiative highlights their common vision for equitable economic growth and the protection of workers' rights. The partnership aims to address issues such as worker exploitation, workplace discrimination, and the clean energy transition. The U.S. hopes to expand the initiative to include additional partners in the future. The officials also discussed the U.S.-Brazil relationship, including Brazil's role as a global leader on climate change and its relationship with China. The officials also mentioned that Haiti will be a topic of discussion in the meeting.